[4] Regional update: ProMED-SoAs
[A] Bangladesh
Date: Thu 7 Oct 2021 18:28 BST
Source: The Daily Star, Star Digital Report [edited]
https://www.thedailystar.net/health/disease/coronavirus/events-who/deaths-infections/news/12-covid-19-deaths-recorded-24-hours-positivity-rate-now-297-2192971


According to a press release issued by the Directorate General of Health Services (DGHS), 12 people died from COVID-19 in 24 hours as of 8 am today [7 Oct 2021]. The total number of COVID-19 deaths in the country now stands at 27 647 and the death rate stands at 1.77%.

A total of 22 321 samples were tested across the country and at least 663 new infections were recorded in this period, taking the total number of people infected to 1 560 818, added the release. The current positivity rate is 2.97% while the overall positivity rate stands at 15.78%.

At least 664 COVID-19 patients have recovered during this period. The total number of recoveries is now 1 521 777 and the recovery rate is 97.5%.

Among the 12 deceased, 6 were men and 6 were women. Of them, one was between 21-30 years old, 2 between 41-50, 5 between 61-70, 3 between 71-80, and one between 81-90 years old, added the release.

