[C] Nepal
Date: Thu 7 Sep 2021 16:50 NPT
Source: The Himalayan Times [abridged, edited]
https://thehimalayantimes.com/nepal/nepals-covid-19-tally-hits-800000-mark-with-667-new-cases


Nepal's coronavirus caseload reached 800 282 on Thursday [7 Oct 2021] with 667 more people testing positive for the infection in the past 24 hours. Meanwhile, the total coronavirus recoveries stand at 773 140 with 911 discharges logged today [7 Oct 2021]. On the other hand, the countrywide COVID-19 mortality toll increased to 11 200 with 8 more fatalities.

As per the latest data provided by the health ministry, a total of 10 672 tests were conducted in the last 24 hours of which 7264 were PCR tests while 3408 were antigen tests. With this, a total of 4 264 067 PCR tests have been carried out to date [7 Oct 2021]. Similarly, antigen tests have confirmed 138 positive cases in the past 24 hours. The total number of single-day infections from both the RT-PCR and antigen tests amount to 804.

Nepal's COVID-19 recovery rate stands at 96.6%, while the fatality rate stands at 1.4%. The country's active COVID-19 case count currently is 15 942. Currently, there are 242 individuals in various quarantine facilities across Nepal.

On Wednesday [6 Oct 2021], Nepal's coronavirus caseload had reached 799 615 with 849 more people testing positive for the infection. The capital district holds the highest number of infections with 207 cases in the country while Jhapa is 2nd in line with 58 cases today [7 Oct 2021].

So far, a total of 14 439 285 people have received coronavirus vaccine across the country, of which 8 008 854 have received the 1st dose while only 6 430 431 individuals have been inoculated with both the doses and are fully vaccinated.

