Pakistan has reported fewer than 1000 new coronavirus cases for the 1st time in 3 months as 912 cases were detected in the last 24 hours. The last time fewer than 1000 cases were recorded was on 5 Jul 2021 when 830 new infections were confirmed.

According to the government's COVID-19 portal, 45 619 tests were conducted during this period. The total number of cases has risen to 1 256 233 and the positivity ratio is 1.99%.

Meanwhile, the death toll has risen to 28 058 after 26 more fatalities were confirmed in the last 24 hours. The breakdown of cases and deaths during the last 24 hours is as follows:

- Punjab: 393 cases, 13 deaths
