[Data by country, area, or territory for 8 Oct 2021 can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/wp-content/uploads/world-pdf/2021%20WHO%20Daily%20Tables%20OCT8_1633800130.pdf.

- The Americas region reported 35.8% of daily case numbers and 46.1% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours and maintained its position as the most severely affected region, having reported more than 91.01 million cases. The USA reported over 112 000 cases in the last 24 hours, followed by Brazil (17 893); 8 other countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours, while 3 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The European region reported 43.2% of daily case numbers and 33.5% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, and total cumulative cases reported exceed 71.49 million cases. Some countries not reporting cases in the last 24 hours or longer include Belgium (3 cases) and Switzerland (1 case), among others; 26 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours, and another 6 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 3.9% of daily case numbers and 5.4% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 15.93 million cases. Iran (11 625) reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours, followed by Iraq, Pakistan, and Occupied Palestinian Territory. Lebanon, Egypt, and Libya reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases. Morocco, Jordan, and Tunisia, among others, reported no cases in the last 24 hours.

- The African region reported 1.1% of daily case numbers and 2.7% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 6.07 million cases. Ethiopia (1166) reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours, followed by South Africa and Nigeria, which both reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases. Many countries, including Cameroon, Gabon, and Benin, among others, reported no cases in the last 24 hours.

- The Western Pacific region reported 7.6% of daily case numbers and 5.8% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 8.78 million cases. Philippines reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours (over 9000 cases), followed by Malaysia, Viet Nam, Singapore, Australia, South Korea, and Japan.

- The South East Asia region reported 8.1% of the daily newly reported cases and 6.4% of reported deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 43.30 million cases. India is dominant, reporting over 21 000 cases over the last 24 hours, followed by Thailand (11 140), Myanmar (1466), Indonesia (1384), Nepal (715), and Bangladesh (645). Sri Lanka and Maldives have not reported any cases for many days.

On the Overview tab at the WHO source URL, the epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 8 Oct 2021, is an excellent visual representation of the pandemic. - Mod.UBA]

